<dl id="n40078b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40078b">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40078b"> 78(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> the sex</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The next point I propose to consider is the position of womanhood in The Nights &hellip; I have glanced at the subject of the sex in Al-Islam to such an extent throughout my notes that little remains here to be added. <small> Richard F. Burton, &ldquo;Terminal Essay&rdquo;, <a name="RBTE2" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#RBTE2"><cite title="source">The Book of the Thousand Nights and a Night</cite></a> (n.d.) X, 192</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
